<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Ambrose_Bierce&amp;action=edit&amp;section=13" title="Edit section: References">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">References</span></h2>
<div class="references-small">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-0"><b><a href="#cite_ref-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/Carlos_Fuentes" title="Carlos Fuentes">Carlos Fuentes</a>, <i>Gringo Viejo</i> (Planeta, 2004) <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9686941673" class="internal">ISBN 9686941673</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-1"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.capstonerecords.org/CPS-8708.html" class="external text" title="http://www.capstonerecords.org/CPS-8708.html" rel="nofollow">Capstone Records:Rodney Waschka II - Saint Ambrose</a></li>
</ol>
</div>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFBleiler2009"><a href="/wiki/Everett_F._Bleiler" title="Everett F. Bleiler">Bleiler, Everett</a> (1948). <i>The Checklist of Fantastic Literature</i>. Chicago: Shasta Publishers. pp.&#160;32, 147.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Checklist+of+Fantastic+Literature&amp;rft.aulast=Bleiler&amp;rft.aufirst=Everett&amp;rft.au=Bleiler%2C+Everett&amp;rft.date=1948&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B32%2C+147&amp;rft.place=Chicago&amp;rft.pub=Shasta+Publishers&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Ambrose_Bierce"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
